value.0: The way you appeared. I assume you've met Arcanys...
What happened?
Hm...  Did he mention anything else aside from the temple? Names?
Hm... Mort'ul may be up to something. Let us make haste to Temple Eldur in the south. We must get there before his minions do!
No time to waste, come!
Yes, child?
A few days ago I've sent him to deliver a message to Arcanys. He should be on his way back.

A few weeks after I've requested your aid in ending Mort'ul's threat, Castle Ishtar was invaded and destroyed by his lieutenant Khrat'ul and a vast army of undead. They killed everyone right before my very eyes...
Yes, almost three weeks had passed before he laid siege on Ishtar. Alas, 20 years have passed since that fateful day, the day I failed my people.
I see. You did seem a bit changed when I saw you. That realm you were taken to must have been one of a magical sort. Search for a wizard named Archanys. He lives up north, in the Shrouded Hills.
Dead? This is troubling... Also this note, it seems to be a message from Arcanys. He's one of the few who still uses ancient Elduran.
There isn't much you can make out on it. The readable parts say: "time has com...", "meet ... ruins" and "Ar'Ishtanu". By the gods!...
No time to explain! Quickly, we must leave and make haste for the ruins of Temple Eldur in the south. We must get there before Mort'ul's minions do!
My child, so much has happened since you've disappeared.

And indeed they have, <FirstName>. A few weeks after I've requested your aid in ending Mort'ul's threat, Castle Ishtar was invaded and destroyed by his lieutenant Khrat'ul and a vast army of undead. They killed everyone right before my very eyes...
Yes, almost three weeks had passed before he laid siege on Ishtar. Alas, 20 years have passed since that fateful day, the day I failed my people.
I don't know what has happened to you, <FirstName>, but we thought you were dead. We kept on waiting for salvation, for you, but it's like you were wiped off the face of the earth....
I see. You did seem a bit changed when I saw you. That realm you were taken to must have been one of a magical sort. I advise you to search for a wizard named Arcanys.
He is one of the only survivors of the siege and he has been secretly looking for a way of stopping Mort'ul's reign over Eldura. He lives up north, in the Shrouded Hills. And one more thing...
A few days ago I've sent one of my remaining faithful guards, Gald, to deliver a message to Arcanys. If you meet him, he might be able to help you on your journey. Go now and may Helm be with you!
Yes, but unfortunately I don't bear good news.
It was Xen. She killed him and almost killed me, but Arcanys, with his last breath, teleported me here. He said something about Temple Eldur.
He was saying something that "Luther must..." but then Xen appeared out of nowhere.
Nothing.
Tell me again about Gald
Tell me again what happened to Eldura.
Continue.
It seems like something has happened to me while I was trapped in Mort'ul's realm.
I think I've found Gald. Unfortunately, he was dead. He had this note on him, but it's all gibberish. <StartAction>[Give Luther the note.]</Start>
What does it say?
What? What's wrong.
I've only been gone for a few hours. I don't understand. You look different! The whole forest seems haunted, it's like all the nine hells have broken loose...
Wait, weeks?
20 years?! It can't be!
<StartAction>[Tell Luther what happened to you]</Start>
